-- 
African Development Bank to Fund Gabon Infrastructure Projects

-- B y   A n t o i n e   L a w s o n
-- 
2011-09-22T16:43:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/african-development-bank-to-fund-gabon-infrastructure-projects.html
Gabon  will receive 400 billion  CFA
francs  ($815 million) from the  African Development Bank  to fund
 road construction , energy and communications projects, said
Moulay Lahcen Ennahli, the lender’s resident representative.  Part of the money, 250 million euros, will be used for the
country’s main highway that connects the capital, Libreville,
with other cities in the central African nation, he said in an
interview in the city today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Antoine Lawson in Libreville via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 